Runaround Isaac Asimov
It was one of Gregory Powell&rsquo;s favorite platitudes that nothing was to be gained from excitement, so when Mike Donovan came leaping down the stairs toward him, red hair matted with perspiration, Powell frowned.
&ldquo;What&rsquo;s wrong?&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;Break a fingernail?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yaaaah,&rdquo; snarled Donovan, feverishly. &ldquo;What have you been doing in the sublevels all day?&rdquo; He took a deep breath and blurted out, &ldquo;Speedy never returned.&rdquo;
Powell&rsquo;s eyes widened momentarily and he stopped on the stairs; then he recovered and resumed his upward steps.
